g.text: Use logical steps to reach Q
Apply logical reasoning to derive intermediate steps:
• Statement has clear logical progression P → Q
• Hypothesis P provides concrete starting point
• Definitions and known results apply directly
• No negations or complex conditional structures
• Constructive proofs where you build the result
If n is even, then n² is even
∴ n = 2k for some integer k (definition of even)
Since 2k² is an integer, let m = 2k²
Conclude: P → Q is proven directly ∎
